snippet.textDisplay: My Dad used to play the original qawali while we drove for Jumma prayer. I remember hating it as a kid not understanding the lyrics, the tabla, the harmonium everything. Here we are 25 years later and I'm in love with the same things I hated about it. It made me proud that my Dad and I have the same taste, Thanks Coke Studio for giving me that feeling and bringing back those memories!... PS: Atif Aslam can sing a phonebook!!
